snippet.textDisplay:
An ode to the uncertainties of life with a parable of a lone boatman on a river with no sight of the other shore (as it often is for Padma, Brahmaputra, and Meghna, three of the mightiest rivers of the country, specially in the rainy season). The somber tunes of the instruments, the apprehensive yet serene vocal, the slow rhythm and the adagio tempo of the whole, did the magic of this track. The lyrics-composition is by Jasimuddin, known affectionately as the ''village poet'' of Bengal, whose poetry reflects the intimate relation of lives and nature in the countryside of Bangladesh.
Thank you Arnob and your team for creating this magic!
